POLYPƲS;
〈 in non-Latin alphabet 〉
is a fleſhly matter growing in the noſtrils, like unto a kind of carbuncle: Hippocrat. Hippocrates doth affirm that it is uncurable.

EPULIS;


      〈 in non-Latin alphabet 〉
   . is a fleſhly excreſcence of the gums, which by little and little oft times is increaſed to the bigneſſe of an egge, ſo that it doth hinder the ſpeech, and eating. It caſts forth Salvious and ſtinking filth, and not ſeldom degenerates into a Cancer, which you may underſtand by the propriety of the colour, pain, and other accidents; and then you muſt not touch it with your hand.

CANCER, It is a hard tumor, rough, and unequall;


      〈 in non-Latin alphabet 〉
   . round and immoveable; of an aſh or livid colour, horrin by reaſon of the veines on every ſide, ſwollen with black blood, and ſpread abroad to the ſimilitude of the ſtretched out legs, and clawes of a crab.
